spanGrp.span: ‘I thought that where the tiger was locked in, he went in to steal.
Yís të begetsá (_) (_) nãmã kablali köte-lë ska (_) (_) jie köwã'ũ jakblö
He locked himself in with the tiger.
Í í wagi jẽk kötiá-wã (_) mãĩ nãmã kablali ska (_)
Then he himself did not know how to get out.
(_) Tögapa ra tögapa í wagi ka yenẽ ka mẽnẽbi í denẽsãũ-nẽ
A lady came to take care of the tiger, (_)
He thought that the lady had seen how he was caressing the tiger;
begetsá-nẽ-nã í í jie të pemi/ (_) pemina je të sũã'/ je të í sũã'-nẽ-nã jie jie të mẽnẽbi nãmã nãmã (_) (_) estee (_) peñẽ-gẽ peñẽ-gẽ
he ran away out of fear and went far away
Jie tunã' köũ (_) suanẽ Jie mẽnẽgãũ komĩ' (_)
and then the lady went to see him.’
